history.content:
I highly doubt they purposely schedule lectures at bad times like that. Room allocation is usually under central campus jurisdiction, so I don't think there's much the EECS staff can do about it.

I think the main reason for terrible lectures is that we just have so many large classes on campus, with very few large lecture halls. Especially this semester with Wheeler closed.

history.content: Actually, if there was an EECS student vote that promised there would be no complaints when upper division courses conflicted as well as no expectation of alternate final exams, we would have fewer evening classes.  There are plusses and minuses of going either way on that one.  (We could also teach more regularly at 8am to avoid evenings and conflicts.)

Hi, not to whine or anything, just wondering if it is possible to move CS classes to a more reasonable time? I have been taking classes with lecture at 6:30-8pm for 3 semesters and I am wondering is there a reason for such a late lecture time?
